# =========================================================
# MIGA-OS MINIMALIST MANIFEST (V1.0)
# Goal: Under 800MB Footprint | Zero Telemetry | Max Speed
# =========================================================

# --- [1. SYSTEM FOUNDATION] ---
# Essential binaries to make the hardware actually boot.
systemd                     # The 'Master Process' that starts everything else.
busybox                     # Replaces 300+ standard tools with one tiny file (Anti-Bloat).
util-linux                  # Core disk and hardware management tools.
udev                        # Detects when you plug in modules or USB devices.

# --- [2. GRAPHICS & DISPLAY] ---
# Modern Wayland-based UI. No heavy desktop environments like GNOME/KDE.
wayland                     # The core display protocol (Faster/Securer than X11).
wayfire                     # Our Window Manager. GPU-accelerated and light.
wf-shell                    # The panel (taskbar) and background manager.
mesa-utils                  # Drivers for Mali (ARM) and Intel/AMD (x86) GPUs.

# --- [3. NETWORKING] ---
# Reliable but lightweight connection management.
networkmanager              # Industry standard for WiFi/Ethernet.
wpa_supplicant              # The security layer for WiFi passwords.

# --- [4. AUDIO & MULTIMEDIA] ---
# Low-latency audio for gaming and coding.
pipewire                    # Modern audio engine (better than PulseAudio).
wireplumber                 # The 'brain' that manages audio routing.

# --- [5. MIGA INTEGRATED SERVICES] ---
# The logic that makes MIGA-OS unique.
python3-minimal             # Tiny Python engine to run our Power/Diag scripts.
zram-config                 # Compresses RAM to boost performance on lower-tier chips.
dbus                        # Allows our Power Daemon to talk to the hardware.

# --- [6. TERMINAL & DEV TOOLS] ---
# The primary interface for MIGA-OS users.
alacritty                   # GPU-accelerated terminal (lowest possible latency).
bash                        # The standard command-line language.
